==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Th
<hw>Th</hw>. <def>In Old English, the article <xex>the</xex>, when the
following word began with a vowel, was often written with elision as if
a part of the word. Thus in Chaucer, the forms <xex>thabsence</xex>,
<xex>tharray</xex>, <xex>thegle</xex>, <xex>thend</xex>,
<xex>thingot</xex>, etc., are found for <xex>the absence</xex>, <xex>the
array</xex>, <xex>the eagle</xex>, <xex>the end</xex>, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thacker</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Thack</ent>⟦br⟧
